es of eqality & \"is\" is a identity operators, which is deal with two variable refer to a same object in memory.\n","\n","**8)** what are logical operators in python ?\n","\n","**ans:** Operators are special symbols which are carry specific action.one of the operator is logical operator including and, or & not.\n","\n","**9)** What is type casting in python ?\n","\n","**ans:** Type casting is one of the conversation,here it can change one data type to another data type in python. example- int(),flote(),dic() etc.\n","\n","**10)** what is difference between explicit and inplicit type casting ?\n","\n","**ans:**\n","\n","(1) Explicit involved to  manual conversation while implicid type casting is involved to automatic conversation.\n","\n"," (2) explicid converting small date type to larger one while implicid converting larger data type to smaller one.\n","\n","**11)** What are the purpose of conditional statement in python ?\n","\n","**ans:** conditional statement is one type of code which can handle one or more conditions & control different branches of execution based on the outcome of logical expression.\n","\n","example-if,else and elif.\n","\n","**12)** How does the elif statement work ?\n","\n","**ans:** elif statment can refers to as (...).\n","\n","(1) it can be used as a place holder for incomplete code.\n","\n","(2) it can be used to indicate a variable number of elements within a type, like -tuple,callable.\n","\n","**13)** What is the difference between for and while loops ?\n","\n","**ans:** For loops- iterates a specific number of times,often over a sequence.\n","while loops - Repeatts a block of code as long as a specific condition is true.\n","\n","**14)** Describe a scenario where a while loop is more suitable than a for loop.\n","\n","**ans:** A while loop is more suitable than a for loop when the number of iterations is not known beforehand and depends on a dynamic condition.\n","scenarios like-\n","\n","1) waiting for user input.\n","\n","2) processing data until a condition is met.\n","\n","3) monitoring a system.\n","\n","4)performing a task until it's done.\n","\n","\n","\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"xW3pwhSD3b17"}}]}